tourBios.curYrHigh: Earned PGA TOUR Latinoamérica conditional status with a T15 finish at the Bogota, Colombia Q-School, an event he closed with a strong 66 in January.
tourBios.carHigh:
2015: Only cut made in seven starts on PGA TOUR Latinoamérica was T42 at the Mazatlán Open in March... Carded a hole-in-one during the opening round of the Guatemala Stella Artois Open in May. Hit an 8-iron from 160 yards for his first ace on PGA TOUR Latinoamérica at the par-three 11th hole at La Reunión's Fuego Maya GC.

2014: Missed the cut at the United Leasing Championship on his first career start on the Web.com Tour.

2013: Only cut made in four starts on PGA TOUR Latinoamérica was T48 at the Personal Classic in December.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: A member of the University of Texas' 2012 NCAA Championship team, where he posted a winning record in match play... Named 2012 All-Big 12 Team... 2003 and 2004 Venezuelan National Junior Champion.
tourBios.personal: If not a professional golfer, says he would be a professional tennis player... Has two older brothers, Carlos and Jhonattan, and a younger brother, Billy... His brother Jhonattan plays on the PGA TOUR, where he won the 2011 Bob Hope Classic... Twitter and Instagram name is @juliocvegas
